Good morning,

Today is Chinese New Year =E2=80=94 =E6=96=B0=E5=B9=B4=E5=BF=AB=E6=A8=82=EF=
=BC=81=E2=80=94 and while this was originally scheduled to be a day off, th=
ere are a host of Big Tech earnings coming out today and tomorrow. I'm part=
icularly interested in management commentary given the news of the last wee=
k, so I'm making a (very rare!) scheduling adjustment: tomorrow I will publ=
ish an Update likely covering Meta and/or Microsoft, and then publish the w=
eekly Stratechery Interview on Friday.

Second, I wanted to apologize again for anyone that had issues last week wi=
th the updates to Stratechery. This was, as you might have surmised, a pret=
ty massive update that extended far beyond the website redesign, including =
significant database changes to Passport. That part actually went fine =E2=
=80=94 the latest version has been running on SemiAnalysis ( https://www.se=
mianalysis.com/ ) for a couple of months =E2=80=94 but we did run into seve=
ral interlocking issues that were related to previous migrations. There wer=
e also a few bugs that only manifested at Stratechery scale, including some=
 CDN issues, some issues related to how the Stratechery bundle works, and m=
addeningly, a third party library update to our UUID encoding library that =
dropped characters for IDs that started 00. It was very much a "when it rai=
ns it pours" situation.

Regardless, I did not deliver the user experience that I want to, and I'm s=
orry.

What is particularly disappointing is that these bugs may have overshadowed=
 the biggest news surrounding the upgrade, which was the addition of the As=
ianometry podcast and newsletter to the Stratechery Plus bundle. Please do =
